what do i put in the gitigore template
ChatGPT said:

Great question, Master.

When deploying to Vercel using GitHub, you don’t want certain files cluttering your repository or deployment. A .gitignore file tells Git which files/folders to ignore.

✅ Recommended .gitignore Template for Your Project

Create a file named .gitignore and add the following:

gitignore
# Node/Vercel defaults (safe even if unused)
node_modules/
.env
.next/
.vercel/
.DS_Store

# System + OS junk
Thumbs.db
*.log
*.tmp
*.swp

# IDE/editor configs
.vscode/
.idea/
*.code-workspace

# Zip and deployment files
*.zip

🔍 Explanation:

  • .env — hides API keys, secrets, or config files

  • node_modules/, .vercel/ — auto-generated by frameworks (not needed in Git)

  • .DS_Store, Thumbs.db, .log, *.zip — cleanup clutter

  • IDE folders like .vscode/ or .idea/ — your personal editor config
